Git empty folders ko track nahi karta, sirf files ko track karta hai.
Empty folder = no tracking.
it will ignore that file no status milega par agar
Empty folder ko track karne ke liye uske andar ek file (usually .gitkeep) add karke git add aur git commit karte hain.
Empty folder → file daalo (.gitkeep).

TWO ATTRIBUTES OF GIT STATUS :</br>
a.>git status -v → git status ke saath staged files ka actual content (diff) bhi dikha deta hai.
Status + staged changes preview.

b.>git status -s → repo ka short/summary status dikhata hai (flags jaise M, A, ??).
Short status view
example :-> ?? testProject/ ka matlab hai folder Git ke liye untracked hai (abhi tak git add nahi hua).
            ?? = untracked file/folder.

$ git status -s
A  index.html
?? testProject/
A ka matlab hai file staging area me Added hai aur next commit ke liye ready hai.
A = Added (staged).

// MUltiple files at once
touch f1.txt f2.txt f3.txt→ ek hi command me multiple empty files create karta hai.
Multiple files ek saath banata hai.

git add . → current directory aur uske sub-folders ki saari changes (new/modified files) staging area me daal deta hai.
Sab kuch stage karta hai.

git add . se hum isliye reframe karte hain kyunki ye unwanted files (debug, temp, secrets) bhi stage kar sakta hai.
Short reasons (yaad rakhne layak):
Galti se extra files add ho jaati hain
Secrets / config leak ho sakte hain
Dirty commits bante hain (hard to review)
Better practice (memory tip):
Selective add karo → git add file1 file2

Agar galti se git add . ho jaye, to files ko staging se hatane ke liye git reset use karte hain.
git rm --cached .txt files
Add undo = git reset.
